 JOHANNESBURG A friend of well-known musician Vusi Nova is pleading with the government to address the increasing levels of violent crime.Nova was hijacked and kidnapped from outside his Melville home earlier on Friday.He was later found.LISTEN: Musician Vusi Nova found stripped down after hijacking It makes me feel very bad simply because I've also been hijacked previously. It's not something you get over easily but I feel something needs to be done because I think our criminals are too free. It's like nothing happens -- people can do what they want when they want and nothing happens to them," said Nova's friend Ntando Bangai, also a musician."I don't know who's going to come up with a solution but something needs to be done. This is not the way we need to live as people. People work hard and some people just come and grab and that's not an occupation I think. eNCA